The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 28 June is 44,055 (5,077.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 June, there were 669 new confirmed cases (77.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 June, there were 408 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 64% (261 extra cases).
